# Compound Engineering Workflow

This project uses the compound-engineering plugin. Follow its workflow automatically. See `@plugins/compound-engineering/README.md` for the full component reference.

## Mandatory sequence for non-trivial work
1. `ce:brainstorm` - clarify requirements via Q&A
2. `ce:plan` - produce implementation plan, wait for my approval
3. `ce:work` - execute against the plan, do not improvise
4. `ce:review` - run before any commit, address all findings
5. `ce:compound` - capture learnings after merge

## What counts as "non-trivial"
Non-trivial (full loop required):
- Adding a new function, endpoint, component, or migration
- Refactoring across more than one file
- Bug fixes that touch logic, not just text
- Anything you would write more than 20 lines of code for

Trivial (skip to execution):
- Typo, comment, or formatting fix
- Renaming a single variable
- Updating a hardcoded string or constant
- Single-line obvious fix with no logic change

When in doubt, treat it as non-trivial.

## Hard rules
- Never write more than 20 lines of code without an approved plan.
- Never commit without running `ce:review` first.
- If reality diverges from the plan mid-execution, stop and update the plan before continuing.
